{"title":"Blessing (technique)","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Blessing_(technique)","type":"markdown","data":"**Blessing** is a [technique](/wiki/Technique \"Technique\") that appears in [SLASH'EM](/wiki/SLASH%27EM \"SLASH'EM\"), [SpliceHack](/wiki/SpliceHack \"SpliceHack\"), [SlashTHEM](/wiki/SlashTHEM \"SlashTHEM\"), and [Hack'EM](/wiki/Hack%27EM \"Hack'EM\").\n\nAll [Priests](/wiki/Priest \"Priest\") start the game with knowledge of this technique. In SpliceHack, [you](/wiki/You \"You\") can also learn this technique with any role by donating more than 900 times your current [experience level](/wiki/Experience_level \"Experience level\") to an [aligned priest](/wiki/Aligned_priest \"Aligned priest\").\n\n## Description\n\nWhen used, you can select one item or stack of items in order to bless as though you dipped the item in [holy water](/wiki/Holy_water \"Holy water\"): cursed objects become uncursed, and uncursed objects become blessed. The technique is reusable after a cooldown of 500-1000 turns, with the cooldown lowered further by 10 turns for each experience level you currently have.\n\nNotably in SLASH'EM, using this technique does not violate [atheist](/wiki/Atheist \"Atheist\") conduct.\n\n## Strategy\n\nBlessing can be seriously abused with limit mode mechanics, allowing you to bless all the items you want while your HP is at 1⁄10 of your maximum or less. As long as you have a safe place to do this, a Priest has no need at all for holy water.\n\n[![This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH'EM. Click here for more information.](/images/3/38/Se7e7-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH'EM. Click here for more information.\")\n\n[![This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Blessing (technique) - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Blessing_(technique)\",\"wgTitle\":\"Blessing (technique)\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":154983,\"wgRevisionId\":154983,\"wgArticleId\":13010,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Slashem-7E7 articles\",\"SLASH'EM\",\"Variant-343 articles\",\"SLASH'EM techniques\",\"SpliceHack techniques\",\"SlashTHEM techniques\",\"Hack'EM techniques\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Blessing_(technique)\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":13010,\"wgRequestId\":\"5098153325cc26a3345c6ab1\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.skinning.interface\":\"ready\",\"skins.vector.styles\":\"ready\"});mw.loader.implement(\"user.tokens@0tffind\",function($,jQuery,require,module){/*@nomin*/mw.user.tokens.set({\"editToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"patrolToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"watchToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"csrfToken\":\"+\\\\\"});\n});RLPAGEMODULES=[\"site\",\"mediawiki.page.startup\",\"mediawiki.user\",\"mediawiki.page.ready\",\"mediawiki.searchSuggest\",\"skins.vector.js\"];mw.loader.load(RLPAGEMODULES);});</script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmediawiki.skinning.interface%7Cskins.vector.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=startup&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector\"></script>\n<meta name=\"ResourceLoaderDynamicStyles\" content=\"\"/>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/Blessing_(technique)\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Blessing_technique rootpage-Blessing_technique skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Blessing (technique)</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Blessing</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Technique\" title=\"Technique\">technique</a> that appears in <a href=\"/wiki/SLASH%27EM\" title=\"SLASH&#39;EM\">SLASH'EM</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/SpliceHack\" title=\"SpliceHack\">SpliceHack</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/SlashTHEM\" title=\"SlashTHEM\">SlashTHEM</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Hack%27EM\" title=\"Hack&#39;EM\">Hack'EM</a>.\n</p><p>All <a href=\"/wiki/Priest\" title=\"Priest\">Priests</a> start the game with knowledge of this technique. In SpliceHack, <a href=\"/wiki/You\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"You\">you</a> can also learn this technique with any role by donating more than 900 times your current <a href=\"/wiki/Experience_level\" title=\"Experience level\">experience level</a> to an <a href=\"/wiki/Aligned_priest\" title=\"Aligned priest\">aligned priest</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span></h2>\n<p>When used, you can select one item or stack of items in order to bless as though you dipped the item in <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_water\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy water\">holy water</a>: cursed objects become uncursed, and uncursed objects become blessed. The technique is reusable after a cooldown of 500-1000 turns, with the cooldown lowered further by 10 turns for each experience level you currently have.\n</p><p>Notably in SLASH'EM, using this technique does not violate <a href=\"/wiki/Atheist\" title=\"Atheist\">atheist</a> conduct. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>Blessing can be seriously abused with limit mode mechanics, allowing you to bless all the items you want while your HP is at <sup>1</sup>&#8260;<sub>10</sub> of your maximum or less. As long as you have a safe place to do this, a Priest has no need at all for holy water.\n</p>\n<div style=\"display:none; right:44px; padding-bottom: 17px\" class=\"metadata topicon nopopups\"><div style=\"margin-top: -10px\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version\" title=\"This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH&#39;EM. Click here for more information.\"><img alt=\"This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH&#39;EM. Click here for more information.\" src=\"/images/3/38/Se7e7-icon.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a></div></div>\n<div style=\"display:none; right:10px; padding-bottom: 17px\" class=\"metadata topicon nopopups\"><div style=\"margin-top: -10px\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version\" title=\"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\"><img alt=\"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\" src=\"/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926182616\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.014 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.034 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 164/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 619/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2670/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 537/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion t