\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul id=\"footer-places\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li id=\"footer-places-about\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:About\" title=\"NetHackWiki:About\">About NetHackWiki</a></li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li id=\"footer-places-disclaimer\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:General_disclaimer\" title=\"NetHackWiki:General disclaimer\">Disclaimers</a></li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul id=\"footer-icons\" class=\"noprint\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li id=\"footer-poweredbyico\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"//www.mediawiki.org/\"><img src=\"/resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png\" alt=\"Powered by MediaWiki\" srcset=\"/resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_132x47.png 1.5x, /resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_176x62.png 2x\" width=\"88\" height=\"31\"/></a>\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgPageParseReport\":{\"limitreport\":{\"cputime\":\"0.014\",\"walltime\":\"0.034\",\"ppvisitednodes\":{\"value\":164,\"limit\":1000000},\"ppgeneratednodes\":{\"value\":619,\"limit\":1000000},\"postexpandincludesize\":{\"value\":2670,\"limit\":2097152},\"templateargumentsize\":{\"value\":537,\"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":8,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"unstrip-depth\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":20},\"unstrip-size\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":5000000},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%   16.696      1 -total\",\" 44.50%    7.429      1 Template:Slashem-7E7\",\" 37.95%    6.336      1 Template:Frac\",\" 30.98%    5.173      2 Template:Version_icon\",\" 19.35%    3.231      2 Template:Top_icon\",\" 16.64%    2.779      1 Template:Variant-343\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240926182616\",\"ttl\":604800,\"transientcontent\":false}}});mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":86});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"'''Blessing''' is a [[technique]] that appears in [[SLASH'EM]], [[SpliceHack]], [[SlashTHEM]], and [[Hack'EM]].\n\nAll [[Priest]]s start the game with knowledge of this technique. In SpliceHack, [[you]] can also learn this technique with any role by donating more than 900 times your current [[experience level]] to an [[aligned priest]].\n\n==Description==\nWhen used, you can select one item or stack of items in order to bless as though you dipped the item in [[holy water]]: cursed objects become uncursed, and uncursed objects become blessed. The technique is reusable after a cooldown of 500-1000 turns, with the cooldown lowered further by 10 turns for each experience level you currently have.\n\nNotably in SLASH'EM, using this technique does not violate [[atheist]] conduct. \n\n==Strategy==\nBlessing can be seriously abused with limit mode mechanics, allowing you to bless all the items you want while your HP is at {{frac|10}} of your maximum or less. As long as you have a safe place to do this, a Priest has no need at all for holy water.\n{{slashem-7E7|offset=1}}\n{{variant-343}}\n[[Category:SLASH'EM techniques]]\n[[Category:SpliceHack techniques]]\n[[Category:SlashTHEM techniques]]\n[[Category:Hack'EM techniques]]"}